save this EASY TOFU SOFRITAS recipe (gf & vegan) 🤩🌱🌯🌮 follow @simplyquinoa for more easy flexitarian recipes!

INGREDIENTS:
1 block extra-firm tofu , drained
2 tablespoons olive oil , divided
1¼ teaspoons kosher salt , divided
1 large yellow onion , diced
3 garlic cloves , minced
1 teaspoons smoked paprika
½ teaspoon chili powder (can add more to taste)
1/2 teaspoon cumin
2 chipotle peppers in adobo
2 tablespoons adobo sauce
1 15-ounce can diced tomatoes
1 tsp granulated sugar

INSTRUCTIONS:
Wrap the tofu in a dish towel and place something heavy on top to press for 30 minutes.

Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Crumble the tofu into very small pieces and add to the skillet. Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt. Cook, undisturbed, until browned and crisp on one side, about 5 minutes. Stir and continue to cook until browned all over, about 10 more minutes, reducing the heat as necessary to avoid burning. Transfer tofu to a plate.

Heat the remaining 1 tablespoon oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the onion and remaining ¼ teaspoon salt and cook until softened and starting to brown, about 5 minutes. Add the garlic, paprika, chili powder, and cumin and cook, stirring, for 1 minute, until fragrant.

Meanwhile, in a blender, combine the chipotle peppers, adobo sauce, tomatoes, and sugar.
Add the sauce and tofu to the skillet and stir well. Bring to a simmer and cook for 2-3 minutes, until heated through.

Serve on burrito bowls, tacos, or a salad.

MORE RECIPES LINKED IN BIO! #sofritas #vegan #veganmeals #flexitarian

HEALTHY INSTANT HOT CHOCOLATE 🍫 😋☃️ follow @simplyquinoa for more healthy recipes! Tis the season for hot cocoa, fires and holiday music, so I wanted to share my version of instant(ish) healthy hot chocolate! Takes about 2 mins to make and has much less sugar than the packets 👏

INSTANT HOT COCOA
2 - 3 tbsp dark chocolate chips
1/2 tsp unsweetened cocoa powder
Sweetener of choice (I like monk fruit extract, but stevia would work well)
1 - 2 cups boiling water
1/2 cup almond milk

INSTRUCTIONS:
- add the chips, cocoa powder and sweetener into your mug
- top with 1/2 - 1 cup boiling water and blend with a handheld frother until melted (about 30 seconds)
- add the rest of your hot water and almond milk and enjoy!

save this HOMEMADE NUTELLA (just 2 ingredients)💥🍫🌰 Follow @simplyquinoa for more healthy recipes!

What you need:
4 cups hazelnuts
⅓-½ cup vegan dark chocolate chips depending on taste

How to:
1. Place hazelnuts on a baking sheet (I used the sheet that comes with my toaster oven) and toast the nuts for 5 minutes.
2. While the nuts are toasting, melt the chocolate in the microwave or over a double boiler.
3. Transfer them to a food processor and process on high until smooth and creamy. Again, you might have to scrape the sides down as you go to help the nuts continue to blend. Once smooth, add the melted chocolate and process again to incorporate.
4. Transfer to a glass container and store in a cool dark place.

Follow @simplyquinoa for more recipes 💚 GREEN BEAN ALMONDINE! A simple side dish made with blanched green beans sautéed in butter and seasoning, then served with toasted almonds 🫶

Here’s what you need:
1 pound green beans , trimmed
½ cup slivered almonds
2 tablespoons vegan butter , or olive oil
3 garlic cloves , grated on a microplane
½ tsp. kosher salt , plus more for salting the water
¼ tsp. lemon zest

Bring a large pot of well-salted water to a boil. Fill a large bowl with ice and cold water. When the water in the pot is boiling, add the green beans all at once and cook for 1 to 2 minutes, until bright green and crisp-tender. Immediately drain the beans and submerge in the ice bath.
Heat a large skillet over medium heat. Add the almonds and toast, stirring constantly, until fragrant and starting to turn golden, about 4 minutes. Sprinkle with a pinch of salt and transfer to a bowl.
Add the butter to the skillet over medium heat. Add the garlic, then add the green beans and ½ tsp. salt, and cook while stirring. Cook until the garlic is fragrant and the green beans are tender, about 1 minute. Add the lemon zest.
Transfer to a platter and top with the almonds. Serve warm or at room temperature.

FULL RECIPE and blog post linked in bio 😍 simplyquinoa.com/green-bean-almondine/

CREAMY PROTEIN OATMEAL 🫶 follow @simplyquinoa for more easy recipes!

This has been my go-to oatmeal all of pregnancy. It’s got 18+ grams of protein PER bowl and it’s sooo creamy. The secret? Whisk in a beaten egg!

*SAVE* this post for when you need a quick, high protein breakfast to make!

WHAT YOU NEED:
1/3 cup oats
1 scoop protein powder
1 tablespoon chia seeds
1 cup+ water or milk
1 egg, beaten
Desired mix-ins
Toppings of choice

TO MAKE:
Add the oats, protein, chia and liquid. Whisk together and bring to a simmer.
Beat the egg in a small bowl and pour into the simmering oats. Whisk immediately until completely incorporated.
Stir in any mix-ins and serve!

finally listening to my body after 8+ years 🫶 and it has transformed how I feel.

I used to avoid most animal proteins. Partly because it’s what I thought was”healthy” and partly because I put myself in a box publicly that I was scared to stray from.

But after speaking to many experts as we were trying to conceive there was one common theme: adding animal proteins and dairy could help improve my nutrient and mineral levels and improve my egg quality. 

I started slowly, but the improvements were almost immediate. More energy, less brain fog, more satisfied between meals and overall feeling like a weight had been lifted.

I focus on quality over quantity when it comes to animal proteins. Grass fed and finished, pasture raised, organic, local. Because not only is it better for me, it’s better for the environment, animals and more. 

This is a personal choice. And I’m sharing because this is a personal page. This is MY choice and MY body. If this way of eating doesn’t work for you, that’s a-okay. That’s YOUR choice 💕

make sure to bookmark this BANG BANG CAULIFLOWER recipe for later 💥🫶 they might taste deep fried but these healthy nuggets are actually twice baked to cunchy perfection! Can be made in the oven or the air fryer 👍

WHAT YOU NEED 👇

for the cauliflower:
1 cup unsweetened almond milk
1 tablespoon apple cider vinegar
2/3 cup flour of choice (I like quinoa)
2/3 cup starch (tapioca, potato, corn, etc.)
1 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder
1 1/2 teaspoon onion powder
1 teaspoon smoked paprika
1 teaspoon kosher salt , plus more for panko
1 tablespoon chili garlic sauce (or sriracha)
1 medium head cauliflower , cut into bite-sized florets
1½ cups gluten-free panko breadcrumbs

for the glaze:
¼ cup maple syrup
1 tablespoon chili garlic sauce (or sriracha) (plus more to taste)
2 tablespoons rice vinegar
1 tablespoon sesame seeds

HOW TO MAKE IT 👇
In a liquid measuring cup, combine the milk and vinegar. Let sit for at least 5 minutes, until curdled.
In a large bowl, combine the flour, cornstarch, garlic powder, onion powder, smoked paprika, and salt.
Add the almond milk mixture and chili garlic sauce and stir to combine. It will be thick.
Place the panko on a large, flat plate. You can start with about half of the panko and add the remaining as you work.
Add about a quarter of the cauliflower florets to the batter mixture and stir to coat the cauliflower. Using tongs, coat each floret in the panko and transfer to a baking sheet.
Preheat the air fryer to 400°F.
Spray the panko-coated cauliflower with cooking spray.
Add cauliflower to the air fryer basket in an even layer, working in batches to avoid crowding the basket. Air fry for 10 minutes, until crispy, turning the cauliflower after 5 minutes.
While this batch cooks, continue battering and breading the remaining cauliflower.
Whisk together the glaze ingredients in a large bowl.
Transfer cooked cauliflower to the bowl with the glaze. Toss to coat evenly. Return cauliflower to the air fryer and cook for 5 more minutes. Repeat with remaining cauliflower and glaze.

Bookmark these EASY CHICKEN LETTUCE WRAPS for a quick dinner idea 👏 they’re ready in about 15 minutes, can easily be made vegetarian by using tempeh and legit have the best sauce!!

WHAT YOU NEED 👇
1 tablespoon grated ginger
2 garlic cloves , minced
3 tablespoons low-sodium soy sauce or tamari
2 tablespoons rice vinegar
2-3 teaspoons sriracha , to taste
1 teaspoon sesame oil
1 tablespoon neutral oil (such as avocado)
1 pound ground chicken
3 scallions , thinly sliced, light and dark parts separated
1 cup shredded carrots
1 cup shredded white cabbage
2 tablespoons sesame seeds
¼ cup chopped fresh cilantro
Large lettuce leaves for serving

HOW TO MAKE 👇
In a small bowl, combine the ginger, garlic, soy sauce, vinegar, sriracha, and sesame oil.

Heat the neutral oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the chicken in one piece and cook, undisturbed, until well browned on the bottom, 2-3 minutes. Flip and brown the other side, breaking the chicken up into 3-4 large pieces. Once the chicken is well browned on both sides, start stirring to break it up into small pieces.

Add the light parts of the scallions, carrots, and cabbage, and stir well. Add the sauce mixture and stir to combine until the chicken is no longer pink and the sauce is evenly distributed. Sprinkle with sesame seeds, the greens of the scallions, and cilantro. Serve in lettuce cups!

KOREAN INSPIRED CRISPY TOFU ✌️✨ share this recipe with your friends and follow @simplyquinoa for more healthy meals!

WHAT YOU NEED:
1 block extra-firm tofu
2 tablespoons soy sauce/tamari
2 tablespoon gochujang or chile-garlic sauce
2 tablespoon rice vinegar
1 tablespoon toasted sesame oil
1 tablespoon maple syrup or coconut sugar
2 garlic cloves, grated
½ cup cornstarch
½ tsp. kosher salt
1 scallion , thinly sliced, for garnish

HOW TO MAKE IT:
1️⃣ Wrap the tofu in a clean dish towel and place something heavy, like a large skillet or cookbook, on top. Drain for 20-30 minutes. *If you’re using shrink-wrapped tofu, you can skip this step.

2️⃣ Preheat the oven or airfryer to 400°F.

3️⃣ Combine the soy sauce, vinegar, gochujang, sesame oil, maple syrup, and garlic in a medium bowl, zip-top bag, or container.

4️⃣ Cut the tofu into ½-inch thick planks. Add the tofu to the soy sauce mixture and toss to coat. Cover and marinate for at least 30 minutes and up to overnight, tossing every so often.

5️⃣ When ready to cook, place the cornstarch and salt in a shallow dish. Working one at a time, dip each tofu piece into the cornstarch mixture, pressing to adhere cornstarch on all sides. Reserve remaining marinade for serving. Spray all of the tofu with cooking spray.

6️⃣ Arrange the tofu on a parchment-lined baking sheet or in the basket of the air fryer, leaving space between each piece. Bake for 20 minutes or airfry for 10, flipping halfway through.

7️⃣ Serve garnished with scallions with remaining marinade for dipping.

FLUFFY BLUEBERRY PANCAKES 🥞🫐 naturally gluten-free and made with wholesome flours! Follow @simplyquinoa for more easy recipes 🫶

WAHT YOU NEED:
1/2 cup sorghum flour
1/2 brown rice flour
1/2 cup quinoa flakes
1/4 cup tapioca flour
2 teaspoons baking powder
1 teaspoon cinnamon
1/4 teaspoon xanthan gum
1/2 teaspoon fine sea salt
2 eggs
1 1/4 cup milk of choice I like almond
2 tablespoons maple syrup
1/2 – 1 cup fresh blueberries

HOW TO MAKE THEM:
1️⃣ Preheat a cast iron skillet or griddle on medium heat.

2️⃣ Whisk all your dry ingredients together in a medium bowl. Beat in your wet ingredients until the batter is smooth and slightly runny, but holds its shape.

3️⃣ Test to see if your pan is hot by flicking water on it. If the water sizzles, you’re ready to cook!

4️⃣ Grease the pan with a bit of cooking spray. Ladle the batter onto the pan and sprinkle with blueberries. 

5️⃣ Cook the pancakes until little bubbles begin to form in the batter, about 2-3 minutes. Flip them over and cook for another few minutes.

6️⃣ Serve with butter and maple syrup, then enjoy!

Being a mom has been one of the most rewarding jobs of my life. But it’s HARD.

I feel like I’ve lost who I used to be. And my identity is now being his mom.

My days revolve around him, and while it’s amazing and I love it, I miss having space. 

So to all my other moms out there who are in the thick of it and feeling lost…

Try creating ONE non-negotiable thing that you do EVERY day that’s for you. Baby can be with you, but it has to fill YOUR cup.

It doesn’t have to be big. Or take a long time.

Just something little that makes you feel like you. 

My non-negotiable? A walk outside.

Seems simple, but it’s literally the breath of fresh air and reset I need. 

Sometimes it’s 10 mins, sometimes is an hour+. But I love it, it makes me feel good and I do it every single day (usually wearing my baby 🤪).

What can you do tomorrow that will make you feel like you again? Share in the comments 😘

And remember: you are amazing. You’re doing your best. You can get through this. I see you and am sending you a big hug 🤗

MOMMOM’S GRAVY 🍝 one of my most treasured recipes in the world! Full recipe below 👇 

INGREDIENTS

For the meatballs:
1 lb ground beef
1/3 lb ground pork
1 egg
1/4(ish) cup breadcrumbs
Splash of milk
Italian seasoning
Salt
Pepper
Romano (optional)
5-6 garlic cloves
Oil for cooking 

For the gravy/sauce:
28oz can crushed tomatoes + 1/2 can of water
14oz can tomato sauce + 1/2 can water
6oz can tomato paste + 1/2 can water
Italian seasoning
Salt & pepper

TO MAKE:
Mix together the meatball ingredients.
Heat the oil and add the garlic. Shape the meatballs and sear on all sides. Set aside. 
Add the sauce ingredients into a large pot. Add the meatballs and any cooking juices (including garlic) and stir to combine. 
Bring to a boil, then reduce to simmer for at least 4 hours. The longer the better!
Serve with your fave pasta and enjoy 😍

3 Habits to Support Digestion 💩

If you’re feeling a little sluggish post-holidays, I’ve got you. Here are three things to focus on NOW that will help you get back into a regular groove of things (if you know what I mean 🤠)

1) STAY HYDRATED 💦

Hydration supports our entire bodies, but especially our digestive system. Aim for at least half your bodyweight in ounces of non-caffeinated liquids per day. Think water (duh), but also seltzer and herbal tea are great too!

Fiber adds bulk to your digestive system and helps to improve regularity. It’s also great at keeping you fuller for longer (which we love). Try to add a fruit and/or veg to every meal if you can!! I have lots of veggie-rich recipes on my blog if you need some inspo 😎
